at|^*B and immediately lay down the spade Ace|
PG| ***** 27 ***** |


pc|sas7s4s3|
PG| ***** 28 ***** |


at| and another spade.^*N|pc|s2s8s5sk|
PG| ***** 29 ***** |


sk||HC|HJ|cp||at| This takes all the trumps out of the Dummy and prevents the Declarer from ruffing his other heart.|
PG| ***** 30 ***** |


NT|^B@2
Eventually he will have to finesse the diamond, and let you get in the lead with your King, after which you can simply lead another heart to Partner's Queen. It is true that overtaking at the first trick is not entirely necessary, and that, if you play a low heart, Partner will probably know enough to lead trumps himself. However, you should never leave to your Partner a decision which you can determine rightly for yourself.|
PG| ***** 31 ***** |


