{ Deciding when to lead trumps on opening lead }
^-|CS|4|CP||AT|
The basic idea is that you should make a trump opening lead when you suspect that dummy has moderate support for partner (at most 3 cards) and that your side has tricks in declarer's side suit that will be ruffed out.|
PG| ***** 71 ***** |


AT|

This most often occurs when declarer has bid 2 suits and dummy has delayed raised one of the suits. One example auction is:|HT|m|at|
{|ia|,1cp1sp2cp2dp2sp4s|at|} |HT|t|AT|^b@2^Z@3In this auction, declarer has shown spades and diamonds and dummy has shown 3 spades. If you as opening leader have some diamond cards, a trump lead is likely to work out, because dummy rates to be short in diamonds (dummy has shows 5+ clubs and 3 spades, leaving him only 5 cards at most in the red suits).|
PG| ***** 72 ***** |


NT||
%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%% Page
HT|e|CS|1|CP|4|AT|
