^-{    Comment By Howard Schutzman -Continued  }

{ When a trump lead may cost you a trick }
^-|CP||CS||AT|^b@2
It is not unusual that a trump lead will cost your side a possible trick, because it will give declarer a free finesse, or at least eliminate a guess. For example, if you lead a trump from 2 or 3 small on an auction where you are pretty sure declarer has exactly an 8 card fit, you will often eliminate the guess of the Q of trumps. So, even if you decide you might want to lead a trump, here are some holdings that are likely to give away tricks:|
PG| ***** 75 ***** |


AT|

a) A singleton trump. It is almost never right to lead trumps if you have a singleton, as it more often than not gives away a trick|
PG| ***** 76 ***** |


AT|

b) Jx, Qx, Jxx, Qxx. If partner has a trump honor, this lead almost always costs your side a trick. |
pg| ***** 77 ***** |


